## 6. Architecture documentation rules

Every time code structure changes, update `FPS_FINDER_ARCHITECTURE.md`.

Must be updated when any of the following changes:
- a new file is created
- data flow changes
- a new endpoint is used
- a new config structure is introduced
- the recommendation algorithm changes
- builder handoff logic changes
- logging changes
- metaobject usage changes

The architecture document must explain:
- what each file does
- how data moves
- which source is canonical
- which parts are runtime serving layers vs authoring layers

