## 7. FPS Finder engineering rules

### 7.1 Keep the feature isolated
FPS Finder should live separately from the main PC Builder wherever possible.

Preferred pattern:
- dedicated section
- dedicated JS asset
- dedicated architecture docs
- reuse stable builder prefill logic rather than modifying it

### 7.2 Keep recommendation logic explainable
Recommendation logic must be understandable by a future developer.

Avoid opaque ranking logic.

### 7.3 Use stateless handoff
FPS Finder result clicks must not require quote-code persistence.

Preferred handoff:
- build prefill link
- open builder
- apply CPU + GPU
- continue in existing flow

### 7.4 Runtime serving model
Do not rely on large Liquid loops over benchmark metaobjects at runtime if avoidable.

Prefer:
- JSON read models
- JS fetch
- JS caching
- flattened lookup shape

### 7.5 Metaobject roles
Treat them as follows:
- `game` metaobject = game identity and display metadata
- `fps_game_profile` metaobject = recommendation rule profile
- `benchmark_entry` metaobjects = benchmark source-of-truth authoring layer
- runtime JSON / JS data = serving layer for FPS Finder UI

